In the summer of 2012 Matrax helped in engineering, producing and developing a sound for newcomer Kat Dahlia alongside a host of talented writers ( Frankie Storm, Meleni Smith, Poison Ivory) and producers (Synamatik, Danny and J Dens) which caught the ear of by Vested In Culture VP of A&R Amanda Berkowitz.
In 2012, describing Dahlia as "more than just a pop artist," Rhone signed her to her newly launched label, Vested In Culture (VIC), a joint venture with Epic Records.
Dahlia's debut album is set to come out in 2013, and will be VIC's inaugural release.
Also in early 2012 Scottishh of Matrax scored a short film called Zero directed by Kim Towens for HBO.
